  "title": "The Witches",
  "description": "In an era of terror and accusation, five women condemned as witches await execution. Facing death, they forge fierce bonds, expose brutal injustice, and rise in defiance. The Witches is a searing tale of resistance, sisterhood, and the unbreakable power of women under tyranny.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Nicole Pontikes + Sarah Jackson<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Sarah Jackson<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Elise Leske, Mila Whiting, Megan Strong, Anna Michelle, Emily Bettenson<br/>",
  "website": "https://www.instagram.com/thewitchesplay",
  "plain_language": "In a time of fear and blame, five women are called witches and sentenced to die. As they wait, they become close, learn the truth about what happened to them, and stand up for themselves. The Witches is a strong story about bravery, friendship, and standing up to unfair treatment.",
